'''Andevor Javin''' was the [[Author/Legends|author]] of a [[Book/Legends|book]] entitled ''[[Carving the Republic: The Real Story of Count Dooku]]''. The book concerned the eponymous [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]],<ref name="News">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|45||A Closer Look}}</ref> who had resigned from his [[Lost Twenty/Legends|postition]] in the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] to found a [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|militarized confederacy]] of [[Planet/Legends|planets]] that wished to secede from the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="The New Essential Chronology">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> On the [[Great ReSynchronization|date]] [[23 BBY/Legends|13:2:28]], according to [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]], Javin's book was number-one on a list of best-sellers.<ref name="News" />

==Behind the scenes==
Andevor Javin was mentioned in [[HoloNet News Vol. 531 45|''HoloNet News Vol. 531 #45'']], a<ref name="News" /> [[2002]]<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=threads/5990764|board=Literature|thread=The Official HoloNetNews Discussion Thread|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/dY0zn}}</ref> [[in-universe]] [[HoloNet News (original website)|website]].<ref name="News" /> [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Paul Ens]] wrote the site content.<ref name="HNN Credits">{{HoloNetNewsWeb||credits.html|Credits}}</ref>

